---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Design. Two Seven Builders"
  description="Design with intent. Site listening, schematic design, and full construction documents for custom homes in the Ottawa Valley."
  active="design"
>
  <section class="hero" style="height:90vh;">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image:url('/images/foundation-pre-build.webp')"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <span class="eyebrow fade-up">Design</span>
      <h1 class="serif fade-up d-1" style="margin-top:18px;">Listen first.<br /><em>Draw second.</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub fade-up d-3" style="margin-top:32px;">Every line on paper has been on the land.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-scroll">Scroll</div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-narrow">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">What design means here</span>
        <h2 class="serif" style="margin:24px 0 36px;">A drawing isn't a decision.<br />It's the record of one.</h2>
        <p class="muted" style="font-size:clamp(18px, 1.4vw, 22px); line-height:1.55;">
          We don't draw a house and then look for a lot to put it on. We walk the parcel first, noting slope, sun, wind, water, and neighbouring rooflines. The place speaks. The architecture follows. The result is a home that feels inevitable, not imposed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap">
    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">01. Site Listening</span>
        <h3 class="serif">The land has the first word.</h3>
        <p>Solar arc, prevailing wind, drainage, mature trees, sightlines you don't want to lose. We document the parcel before sketching, sometimes for weeks, in every season we can. The cost of getting siting wrong is paid for the life of the house.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/foundation-pre-build.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">02. Schematic Design</span>
        <h3 class="serif">Big moves, made early.</h3>
        <p>The plan-level decisions like orientation, massing, room adjacencies, and roof geometry are settled before any detail is drawn. Get these right and the rest is tuning. Get them wrong and no detail will save you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/framed-with-windows.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">03. Construction Documents</span>
        <h3 class="serif">Drawings precise enough to build from.</h3>
        <p>Wall sections, flashing details, mechanical coordination, structural sign-off. Every page is vetted before bidding. Vague drawings produce vague buildings. Ours don't leave room for guessing on site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/attention-to-detail.webp')"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="hp-row reveal">
      <div class="hp-text">
        <span class="num">04. Materials &amp; Specifications</span>
        <h3 class="serif">Chosen for forty years, not a photograph.</h3>
        <p>Stone that weathers. Wood that earns its grain. Hardware that stays tight. We specify materials we'd live with, and we'll tell you when a beautiful idea will look tired in a decade.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-img" data-parallax="0.08" style="background-image:url('/images/attention-to-detail-2.webp')"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bone">
    <div class="wrap" style="text-align:center;">
      <h2 class="serif split-text" style="max-width:24ch; margin:0 auto;">Where you build matters. So does <em>who.</em></h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="margin-top:48px;">Start the Process <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
